Trust of land

[The trust of land declared below is made pursuant to Matrimonial Causes Act 1973, section 24(1)(b).] With effect from [the making of this order] / [the date of [decree absolute] / [the final [divorce] / [dissolution] order]] [the family home] / [other property name(s)] shall be held by the applicant and the respondent upon a trust of land for themselves as beneficial tenants in common [in equal shares] / [as to [percentage]% to the applicant and as to [percentage]% to the respondent] upon the following terms:

the [applicant] / [respondent] shall be entitled to occupy the property rent free to the exclusion of the [respondent] / [applicant] until the determining event as defined below;

